page.title: 14Woolley Scout Camp
page.content: On May 30th we visited Woolley camp site. It was built in 1962 and the land cost Â£650. Over 3,000 cubs and scouts camp there every year. I camped there with Newmillerdam cub pack. When everyone was there Akele blew the whistle twice and we all ran to her. She said you can explore the woods, so we went to the top. I went with Alexander and Matthew. When Akele blew the whistle again we all had to run down. Then we had a game of football. At ten we got our beds out but we didn't get to sleep till 2.30 and we woke up at five.At five past seven we had a drink of tea and got dressed.In the day we did some work for a badge. Our team won the trophy.
